			"3-minute hard enrage - if not defeated, Lillian one-shots players with melee attacks. Ambition grants stacks of Ambitious Pursuit for every 10% total raid health missing (5% haste per stack) - maintain high raid health at all times. Tanks swap on Debilitating Strike (40,000 heal absorption per hit). Rogue or Druid tanks recommended for strong mitigation. Scarlet Grasp grips entire raid to center - 3 players get green Unstable Concoction circles and must run to edges while everyone else STANDS STILL. Ignite applies raid-wide Fire damage - use Fire Protection Potions, Frozen Runes, health pots, and immunities. Players with yellow Noxious Poison circles drop them at room edges, then get shielded before expiration. Movement Phase requires constant movement - reaching 5 stacks stuns you and causes heavy damage. At 4 minute mark, Putress begins casting Poison Bolt indefinitely (soft enrage). Use all DPS cooldowns and burn boss as fast as possible.",
			{
				role = DAMAGE,
				"Maximize DPS from the start - this is the tightest DPS check in the raid with only 3 minutes before hard enrage. During Scarlet Grasp, stand completely still unless you have green Unstable Concoction circle. If you have green circle, sprint to room edge immediately. During Ignite, use Fire Protection Potions, Frozen Runes, health potions, and immunity abilities. If targeted by yellow Noxious Poison circle, place it at room edge then get shielded before it expires. During Movement Phase, maintain constant movement to avoid reaching 5 stacks of Intoxicating Venom (stun + heavy damage). Use all offensive cooldowns early and maintain maximum uptime.",
			},
			{
				role = HEALER,
				"Maintain raid at highest health possible - every 10% total missing health grants Lillian 5% haste via Ambitious Pursuit, creating snowball effect. Priority heal tank with Debilitating Strike's 40,000 heal absorption before swapping. Prepare massive healing cooldowns for Ignite (raid-wide Fire damage for 15 seconds). Shield players with yellow Noxious Poison circles before their debuff expires. During Scarlet Grasp, heal while standing still (unless you have green circle). Coordinate all healing cooldowns as fight progresses - falling behind on healing makes fight exponentially harder due to Ambition mechanic.",
			},
			{
				role = TANK,
				"Rogue or Druid tank strongly recommended due to high avoidance and mitigation needs. Swap on every Debilitating Strike - each strike deals 35 Physical damage twice and applies 40,000 heal absorption per hit (80,000 total). Swapping tank must taunt immediately to prevent Lillian from meleeing DPS during her increased haste phases. Maintain defensive cooldowns and communicate with healers about heal absorption amounts. Position boss to give raid room for Scarlet Grasp mechanics.",
			},
